<% provide(:title, "Flows") %>

<div class='top-nav-button'>
    <%= link_to '[back]', learning_path %>
    <%= link_to '[new flow]', new_flow_path %>
</div>

<h1>Flows</h1>

<p>Flow is a tool to control tasks.</p>

<p>
    First, you create a task.
    Keep you tasks as a to-do list.
</p>

<p>
    Each task consists of:
    <ul>
        <li>steps</li>
        <li>resources</li>
        <li>status</li>
    </ul>
    Videos to watch.
    Articles to read.
    Best videos and articles I save to a verified (recommended) list.
</p>

<ul class = 'index-list'>
    <% @flows.each do |flow| %>
    <li><%= link_to flow.title, flow_path(flow) %></li>
    <% end %>
</ul>